text: {| |} Mary Rose was a 24-gun fourth-rate frigate built for the Royal Navy in the 1620s.The "HMS" prefix was not used until the middle of the 18th century, but is sometimes applied retrospectively Commissioned in 1624, she played a minor role as a Parliamentarian ship in the English Civil War. The ship was wrecked in a storm off the Flanders coast in 1650. ==Construction and commissioning== ==Notes== ==Citations== ==Bibliography== * * Category:Ships built in Deptford Category:1620s ships Category:Frigates of the Royal Navy Category:Maritime incidents in 1650
